! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|v0.1.69 |2026-06-09 |''Fix: Instances Overview edge selection now persists across reload.'' The edge-selector stored its titlelist in a field literally named `fields`, which collides with the TiddlyWeb sync wire-format's reserved `fields` container (`tiddlywebadaptor.js` puts every non-standard field into a hashmap named `fields`) ‚Äî so the value was silently dropped on every browser‚Üíserver save and the graph always reverted to the `parent` default. Renamed the field to `edges` in both the //Instances Overview// config tiddler and the //Context// preview state tiddler (`config-instances-overview-edge-fields.tid`, `instances-overview.tid`, `palette/preview/context.tid`); the read also floors to `parent` when unset (`~[[parent]]`), so the default edge is always drawn and the `parent` checkbox shows ticked by default. Edges keep the native checkbox UI. Shadow/template tiddlers ‚Äî re-read on render, but a server restart is needed to pick up the renamed shadow default. |
|v0.1.68 |2026-06-08 |''Quick-create, per-ref "Manage‚Ä¶" actions, and a duration widget'' (all in `cascade-helpers.tid` + one new provider tiddler; needs cascade-palette ‚â•0.0.123). ''(1) Quick-create (`kind.qc-*`).'' A reduced create drill that shows only a declared subset of fields, prefills the rest, and derives the `caption` from a per-action formula ‚Äî the formula lives on a `<draft>/qcmeta` sidecar (so its brackets never become a filter operand) and is recomputed via an injected `ca-on-commit` on each edited field, so a dated caption flows into a unique slug title through the existing title-formula. Safety net: any required-but-unsatisfied field still surfaces as an edit row, and the reused Save row ‚õî-blocks until valid. ''(2) Per-ref "Manage‚Ä¶" actions.'' New `palette/manage-refs-provider.tid` (tagged `‚Ä¶/cascade-palette/action-provider`) + `kind.manage-ref-actions`: surfaces one ''"Manage <field>‚Ä¶"'' action per reference field on any kind instance, drilling straight into the existing ref picker (multi ‚Üí add/remove toggles, single ‚Üí pop-select). ''(3) Duration widget'' (consumes cascade-palette's new `daterange` kind). `kind.qc-range-fields` emits a `daterange` row for a paired start/end (e.g. `when`/`until`) with per-action default offsets + the caption-refresh on-commit; `kind.edit-range-items` binds a `daterange` directly to an ''existing'' record for in-place duration editing (seed-when-empty leaves current values intact). Shadow/Macro tiddlers ‚Äî re-read on render, no restart needed. |Cascade-palette ref / enum field pickers now show the ''currently-selected entries on top, the rest alphanumerically by displayed name'' (`cascade-helpers.tid`). The picker drill (`kind.collection-build`, used by every ref / enum field ‚Äî single & multi) gains `ca-sort-rows: name`, opting its rows into cascade-palette's data-row sort: multi-select toggles that are currently on float to the top (the palette reads the toggle's bind state), then the rest sort by their resolved display name (caption). For single-select `leaf` pickers (ref + enum), which carry no bind state, the row matching the current field value is marked `ca-selected: yes` (new `kind.collection-is-current` helper + `kind.ref-leaf-build2` / `kind.enum-leaf-build`) so the palette can float it too. Needs cascade-palette ‚â•0.0.122. ''Touches:'' `cascade-helpers.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Shadow tiddler only (Macro definitions) ‚Äî re-read on render, no restart needed. |
|v0.1.66 |2026-06-04 |Kind icon lens now declares `ca-lens-actions: via-entity-type` ‚Äî it owns the kind ''Open / Edit / Delete'' actions through cascade-palette's new lens-action bridge, so those actions stay available on every kind row even when the ''Icon'' lens slot is turned off (the actions are always-on, gated only by `ca-lens-when`, never by slot selection). Behaviour-preserving for users; declarative for the new contract. Needs cascade-palette ‚â•0.0.111. |
|v0.1.65 |2026-06-04 |Cascade-palette "Kind icons" migrated from the removed structure-toggle to a ''Kind'' icon ''lens'' (`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/lens`, slot `icon`, gated by `ca-lens-when` on kind types existing). Selectable in the palette's ''Icon'' slot strip; same behaviour (each kind instance shows its `kind.icon`, off by default, persists across reloads). Needs cascade-palette ‚â•0.0.110. |
|v0.1.64 |2026-06-04 |Graph tooltip node actions + modal: hover tooltip on every kind-graph node (Instances Overview + Context preview) gains ''edit'' (live field editor in a modal), ''delete'' (confirm dialog; disabled with a hint while the node has `parent`-field children ‚Äî guard re-checked in the modal) and ''Add child'' buttons for every kind whose `parent` ref field accepts the node's type (plus `kind.parent-kinds` children, `kg.child-kinds`). Create reuses the standard editor + `kind.finalize-create` with parent pre-filled and defaults applied. New `$:/plugins/rimir/kind/graph-modal` overlay (`$:/tags/AboveStory`, layered above the cascade-palette); tooltip buttons dismiss the graph popup on click. |
|v0.1.63 |2026-06-03 |Cascade-palette "Kind icons" structure toggle ‚Äî when on, every menu row backed by a kind instance shows its type's `kind.icon` glyph at the front (all views, persists across reloads). Off by default; appears only while a kind type exists. Needs cascade-palette ‚â•0.0.109. |
